Currently cache is only used to store query result (by segment or whole). But it also can store some pricy calculations such as dim filters. With some non-trivial filter like,

```
"filter" : {
    "type" : "or",
    "fields" : [ {
      "type" : "in",
      "dimension" : "dimMultivalEnumerated",
      "values" : [ "Bar", "Baz", "Foo" ]
    }, {
      "type" : "in",
      "dimension" : "dimMultivalEnumerated2",
      "values" : [ "apple", "orange" ],
      "extractionFn" : {
        "type" : "lower"
      }
    } ]
  }
```

I got the result,

```
Benchmark                                     (numSegments)  (rowsPerSegment)           (schemaAndQuery)  (useFilterCache)  Mode  Cnt      Score      Error  Units
TimeseriesBenchmark.queryMultiQueryableIndex              1            750000  basic.dimFilterByInterval             false  avgt   25  40518.218 ±  817.097  us/op
TimeseriesBenchmark.queryMultiQueryableIndex              1            750000  basic.dimFilterByInterval              true  avgt   25  27264.105 ± 1046.797  us/op
```

To access cache instance from engine and segments, I've moved two classes (Cache and CacheStats) from server module to processing.
And also to make use of `getCacheKey()` on DimFilter class, I've changed some methods to accept DimFilter rather than Filter.

